1
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:04,480
♫ Almost paradise ♫

2
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:08,350
♫ Warmer even than the sun ♫

3
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:12,130
♫ The way you look at me ♫

4
00:00:12,130 --> 00:00:17,780
♫ Feels like I have the whole world ♫

5
00:00:17,780 --> 00:00:19,820
[Boys Over Flowers]

6
00:00:33,699 --> 00:00:35,299
Are you okay?

7
00:00:35,299 --> 00:00:36,999
Yeah.

8
00:00:38,499 --> 00:00:40,866
Even if you weren't okay, you're not the type who would tell me.

9
00:00:40,866 --> 00:00:43,433
I'm really okay.

10
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,877
Wait just a little while.

11
00:00:45,877 --> 00:00:51,189
This time, honestly, even if I have to leave my home,

12
00:00:51,904 --> 00:00:54,521
I'm going to protect you.

13
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:56,422
What are you saying?

14
00:00:57,485 --> 00:01:02,540
The Witch's personality isn't the kind to sit back and do nothing.

15
00:01:02,540 --> 00:01:05,121
She's definitely up to something.

16
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:08,322
I'm just saying that I'll be preparing too.

17
00:01:08,322 --> 00:01:10,989
Don't do that.

18
00:01:10,989 --> 00:01:12,127
What?

19
00:01:12,127 --> 00:01:14,931
Whatever you do, you have to be the reason for it.

20
00:01:14,931 --> 00:01:16,785
I don't want you protecting me.

21
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:18,579
Why do you not like it?

22
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:22,571
Because you're my girl, it's a given that I'd protect you.

23
00:01:24,980 --> 00:01:28,036
Protecting someone and watching over someone...

24
00:01:28,036 --> 00:01:31,505
If that is the only reason that keeps the relationship going, then I don't want it.

25
00:01:32,389 --> 00:01:38,963
Until now, I've already received so much from you, F4 sunbaes, even Jae Kyung unnie.

26
00:01:40,283 --> 00:01:44,050
At the very least, I want you and I to be on equal footing.

27
00:01:44,050 --> 00:01:46,765
As I overcome what needs to be overcome.

28
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:49,351
Do you know?

29
00:01:49,351 --> 00:01:50,666
What?

30
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:56,383
You're the type of girl on whom "cuteness" is wasted.

31
00:02:05,396 --> 00:02:07,700
Huh, what's wrong with you?

32
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,500
Chan! What's wrong?

33
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,900
Why are you so sad? What's wrong?

34
00:02:14,211 --> 00:02:16,017
What?!

35
00:02:16,017 --> 00:02:17,560
Is this the time to be laughing?

36
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:21,790
Hold it in. You'd better hold it in!

37
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:28,810
♫ I didn't know I would do this ♫

38
00:02:28,810 --> 00:02:33,900
♫ Flustered and confused ♫

39
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,860
Wow.

40
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,450
Chan, what is that?

41
00:02:40,450 --> 00:02:41,718
Can you see that?

42
00:02:41,718 --> 00:02:43,855
You can't see it well, huh?

43
00:02:45,755 --> 00:02:47,809
Let me ride on your shoulders, okay?

44
00:02:47,809 --> 00:02:50,467
- What?
- A shoulder ride.

45
00:02:52,223 --> 00:02:54,550
- Is it fun?
- Yes.

46
00:02:56,499 --> 00:02:59,200
He's going to fall.

47
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:02,000
No, I'm not going to fall.

48
00:03:03,790 --> 00:03:06,180
Chan, how do you feel?

49
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:08,580
I'm the tallest.

50
00:03:19,129 --> 00:03:23,433
It must be spring... the weather's mellowed.

51
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:24,738
It's weird.

52
00:03:24,738 --> 00:03:26,600
What is?

53
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:29,518
I feel as though

54
00:03:29,518 --> 00:03:32,739
I'm in a vague dream

55
00:03:32,739 --> 00:03:35,050
that I've had before.

56
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:41,550
I'm just saying...

57
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:44,413
How come this small kid's so heavy!

58
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,583
Hey, Manager Jung.

59
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:56,916
Young master, I think you'd better come back now.

60
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:59,383
Madam Chairman will find you.

61
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,580
Go.

62
00:04:16,316 --> 00:04:17,950
Chan... Oops...

63
00:05:12,725 --> 00:05:19,640
Happy birthday to you! Happy birthday to you!

64
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:27,018
I love you Yi Jung! Happy birthday to you!

65
00:05:27,018 --> 00:05:29,743
Happy birthday, Yi Jung.

66
00:05:29,743 --> 00:05:32,921
Come on, you should make a wish and blow out the candles.

67
00:05:54,856 --> 00:05:56,984
This is a gift.

68
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:17,530
[One meeting, one opportunity]

69
00:06:18,427 --> 00:06:20,359
"One meeting, one opportunity".

70
00:06:20,359 --> 00:06:22,223
What does it mean?

71
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:27,166
A once-in-a-lifetime fate.

72
00:06:39,803 --> 00:06:41,614
Ga Eul.

73
00:06:43,983 --> 00:06:46,218
Yi Jung sunbae...

74
00:06:46,218 --> 00:06:48,606
I found it.

75
00:06:48,606 --> 00:06:50,069
What?

76
00:06:50,069 --> 00:06:52,350
I finally found it.

77
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:59,230
♫ Everything that caught my eyes, everything ♫

78
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:06,130
♫ Is a memory that is connected with you ♫

79
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:13,010
♫ If I tell you that I have come to love you truly, ♫

80
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:21,020
♫ I'm afraid you would be in a difficult place ♫

81
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:29,180
♫ I try calling you again, like this ♫

82
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:35,410
♫ because it's you, you whom I love ♫

83
00:07:35,410 --> 00:07:40,140
♫ I'm going to meet you now ♫

84
00:07:40,140 --> 00:07:50,960
♫ Love deeper than tears, ♫

85
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,352
On that day,

86
00:07:53,352 --> 00:07:57,287
sunrise was at 7 a.m.

87
00:07:58,524 --> 00:08:05,030
This was only visible right at sunrise, for just a few seconds.

88
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:07,157
That message.

89
00:08:16,614 --> 00:08:18,310
Idiot.

90
00:08:20,413 --> 00:08:23,493
Even knowing I was an idiot...

91
00:08:23,493 --> 00:08:27,114
She knew it better than anyone in the whole world.

92
00:08:27,114 --> 00:08:29,970
How could she give me such a tough problem to solve?

93
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:36,300
♫ Because it's you who's alive there ♫

94
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:45,070
♫ I'm going to meet you now ♫

95
00:08:46,050 --> 00:08:48,672
Yi Jung.

96
00:08:48,672 --> 00:08:52,844
I really would like for you to show up.

97
00:08:54,826 --> 00:08:56,960
The breeze

98
00:08:57,850 --> 00:09:03,089
can't go back to a place it has already left, Yi Jung.

99
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:06,692
Do it over! Do it over!

100
00:09:06,692 --> 00:09:09,561
Let me redo it!

101
00:09:37,219 --> 00:09:42,034
Yesterday, the lovely spring weather

102
00:09:42,034 --> 00:09:48,720
brought out many families to the city zoo, where flowers were in full bloom.

103
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:51,780
[Many family outings with good Spring weather]

104
00:10:40,452 --> 00:10:42,288
Mr. President.

105
00:10:42,288 --> 00:10:45,557
Are you serious about keeping this buried?

106
00:10:45,557 --> 00:10:49,929
Even if they say it was an accident that a zealot committed?

107
00:10:49,929 --> 00:10:53,499
It's not as though it would bring these two back to life.

108
00:10:54,167 --> 00:10:57,737
I can't let Ji Hoo see his father and mother's death

109
00:10:57,737 --> 00:11:01,007
be used in political strife.

110
00:11:01,007 --> 00:11:03,024
President.

111
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:09,000
[The late Yoon]

112
00:11:18,504 --> 00:11:24,263
I had no fear about something that I always believed was right.

113
00:11:26,232 --> 00:11:28,610
But it wasn't until after

114
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:34,300
I lost them that I realized that was also a form of arrogance...

115
00:11:36,109 --> 00:11:39,945
It was because of the fear that I might also lose you.

116
00:11:42,281 --> 00:11:46,819
The years that I was unable to see you were my punishment.

117
00:11:49,388 --> 00:11:51,910
When you should have been blaming your Grandfather,

118
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:56,660
you had been living with that terrible burden.

119
00:11:58,397 --> 00:12:01,100
Now, even if I die,

120
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:03,936
I have no regrets, child.

121
00:12:06,371 --> 00:12:09,709
Can I ask that you take care of

122
00:12:09,709 --> 00:12:12,110
the Foundation and the clinic?

123
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:17,750
It was your father and mother's wish

124
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:22,090
to cure the heart by the arts

125
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:25,250
and to cure illness by medical practice.

126
00:12:25,858 --> 00:12:28,360
Grandfather, I'm not yet...

127
00:12:32,298 --> 00:12:34,133
Come over here!

128
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:37,269
Spicy fish soup is ready!

129
00:12:39,271 --> 00:12:42,574
That kid sure has a loud voice.

130
00:12:44,517 --> 00:12:48,530
You're going to chase away all the fish with that loud voice of yours!

131
00:12:48,530 --> 00:12:50,070
This brat.

132
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:51,980
Where is she?

133
00:12:53,219 --> 00:12:54,920
Is it all done?

134
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,300
Yes.

135
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:57,840
Let me see?

136
00:13:04,830 --> 00:13:05,865
How is it?

137
00:13:05,865 --> 00:13:09,793
You rascal, know that I'll eat it because I don't want to waste the perfectly good fish.

138
00:13:12,537 --> 00:13:15,507
Ji Hoo, why don't you taste it?

139
00:13:23,483 --> 00:13:28,487
Amazingly, it tastes a lot like your mom's.

140
00:13:34,626 --> 00:13:37,363
Ok, you two, look over here!

141
00:13:37,363 --> 00:13:40,932
One... two... three!

142
00:14:05,624 --> 00:14:08,927
I have good news and bad news.

143
00:14:08,927 --> 00:14:11,263
Which one do you want to hear first?

144
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:18,570
Ah, I know your style.

145
00:14:18,570 --> 00:14:20,639
Bad news first?

146
00:14:23,509 --> 00:14:28,544
I probably will not be as good as before.

147
00:14:32,351 --> 00:14:34,153
This hand,

148
00:14:35,121 --> 00:14:37,889
whether the pottery gods will choose it again,

149
00:14:37,889 --> 00:14:39,325
I don't know.

150
00:14:39,325 --> 00:14:43,195
No, it won't be that way. They will.

151
00:14:45,264 --> 00:14:49,701
But, what's the good news?

152
00:14:50,702 --> 00:14:54,205
Even with all that, the fact that I will continue.

153
00:14:55,274 --> 00:14:57,942
I'm not going to avoid it anymore.

154
00:14:57,942 --> 00:15:02,548
If you give up once, how much you regret it,

155
00:15:02,548 --> 00:15:05,083
I learned thanks to you.

156
00:15:05,718 --> 00:15:07,852
Sunbae.

157
00:15:08,954 --> 00:15:12,090
Ga Eul, do you want to try it?

158
00:15:22,991 --> 00:15:28,691
How did you know that I would listen the bad news first?

159
00:15:29,790 --> 00:15:35,187
Because good girls like happy endings.

160
00:15:49,651 --> 00:15:55,785
I definitely am a cool guy, but not a good guy.

161
00:15:57,535 --> 00:16:02,786
You need to get rid of your misconception that good girls want good guys.

162
00:16:20,789 --> 00:16:22,669
Yes, mom.

163
00:16:23,314 --> 00:16:24,754
What?

164
00:16:25,387 --> 00:16:27,371
Is that true?

165
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:32,074
All right. I'll be there right away.

166
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:46,430
Alright.

167
00:16:47,450 --> 00:16:51,583
We worked really hard through the Foundation,

168
00:16:51,583 --> 00:16:55,605
and the hard efforts of a lot of people went into this.

169
00:16:57,395 --> 00:17:00,747
Jan Di, take a walk around.

170
00:17:00,747 --> 00:17:02,448
Okay.

171
00:17:07,082 --> 00:17:08,624
It's quite something, isn't it?

172
00:17:08,624 --> 00:17:10,490
It's so spacious.

173
00:17:10,490 --> 00:17:11,732
Oh! What's that grandpa?

174
00:17:11,732 --> 00:17:14,553
Over there are all meeting rooms.

175
00:17:15,762 --> 00:17:17,574
Hold on a second.

176
00:17:18,646 --> 00:17:20,709
Yes, it's me.

177
00:17:21,946 --> 00:17:24,070
Hey, is that true?

178
00:17:25,155 --> 00:17:27,213
Who would have the nerve?

179
00:17:28,011 --> 00:17:31,110
How on earth did this situation come about?

180
00:17:32,545 --> 00:17:33,971
No!

181
00:17:33,971 --> 00:17:38,150
Whatever happens, we must take care of the Foundation!

182
00:17:39,605 --> 00:17:41,887
No!

183
00:17:41,887 --> 00:17:44,160
Grandpa! Grandpa!

184
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:46,126
Grandpa!

185
00:17:46,126 --> 00:17:48,728
Grandpa! Grandpa!

186
00:17:48,728 --> 00:17:51,830
Grandpa, your medicine! The medicine!

187
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,650
Grandpa.

188
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,872
Grandpa...

189
00:17:57,872 --> 00:18:02,141
Sunbae! The hospital, the hospital!

190
00:18:53,226 --> 00:18:56,735
He did not want you to know.

191
00:18:58,163 --> 00:19:01,632
He said he'd be fine as long as he was careful.

192
00:19:05,395 --> 00:19:09,408
Let's go and get Grandfather's things.

193
00:19:32,699 --> 00:19:36,039
The preparations are going well, I presume.

194
00:19:36,039 --> 00:19:37,704
Chairwoman,

195
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:43,406
apart from anything else, could you reconsider regarding the Sooam Foundation?

196
00:19:43,406 --> 00:19:46,479
You know better than anyone that

197
00:19:46,479 --> 00:19:49,284
I'm not doing this out of greed for the silly Foundation.

198
00:19:51,917 --> 00:19:54,220
What are you intending to do?

199
00:19:55,141 --> 00:19:57,518
With this chance, I'm going to pull out the roots.

200
00:19:57,518 --> 00:20:02,895
It's so fortunate that that little upstart child values something more than money.

201
00:20:12,077 --> 00:20:14,436
I have a proposition.

202
00:20:14,436 --> 00:20:16,408
A proposition?

203
00:20:16,408 --> 00:20:18,777
The fact that the marriage didn't happen,

204
00:20:18,777 --> 00:20:21,413
I'm sorry about that.

205
00:20:21,413 --> 00:20:23,549
But,

206
00:20:23,549 --> 00:20:27,653
it's not like the ties are completely cut with JK Group.

207
00:20:27,653 --> 00:20:30,623
I will do my utmost to save it.

208
00:20:30,623 --> 00:20:32,291
Trust in me.

209
00:20:33,927 --> 00:20:35,294
And so what?

210
00:20:35,294 --> 00:20:40,299
Whether you put spies on me or keep me locked up,

211
00:20:40,299 --> 00:20:42,301
I'll take whatever you dish out.

212
00:20:42,301 --> 00:20:43,937
Except.

213
00:20:43,937 --> 00:20:45,771
Except...

214
00:20:45,771 --> 00:20:47,607
Leave Jan Di

215
00:20:48,841 --> 00:20:50,609
alone.

216
00:20:53,145 --> 00:20:56,782
If I don't do anything to Geum Jan Di, then is that enough?

217
00:20:57,683 --> 00:20:59,451
Yes.

218
00:20:59,451 --> 00:21:01,920
I'll make that promise.

219
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:05,825
I won't lift a finger against Geum Jan Di.

220
00:21:06,626 --> 00:21:11,227
In return, don't forget what you've said just now.

221
00:21:11,227 --> 00:21:13,099
Don't worry.

222
00:21:51,871 --> 00:21:55,641
This isn't the time to be moping around.

223
00:21:57,310 --> 00:21:58,911
Granny?

224
00:22:04,751 --> 00:22:09,354
Do you still not know your mother?

225
00:22:09,354 --> 00:22:12,557
This is not the time for you to feel at ease.

226
00:22:12,557 --> 00:22:15,995
When you can't even take care of your own girl,

227
00:22:15,995 --> 00:22:20,532
how do you plan on taking care of Shinhwa Group in the future?

228
00:22:22,201 --> 00:22:26,639
I did not raise you to be such a pathetic man.

229
00:22:26,639 --> 00:22:31,443
Just because a person is born as a male, doesn't mean you're automatically a man.

230
00:22:31,443 --> 00:22:35,481
Since you're furious at your defeat, you can't bear to step back,

231
00:22:35,481 --> 00:22:38,618
and you're embarrassed about running away,

232
00:22:38,618 --> 00:22:44,757
you overcome your weak character over time.

233
00:22:44,757 --> 00:22:49,194
That's how you become a real man.

234
00:22:50,029 --> 00:22:52,564
Do you understand?

235
00:22:58,938 --> 00:23:00,706
Granny!

236
00:23:04,410 --> 00:23:06,278
Thank you.

237
00:24:26,050 --> 00:24:30,470
[Yoon Ji Hoo]

238
00:24:47,949 --> 00:24:53,985
[Ji Hoo in Kindergarten]

239
00:24:54,789 --> 00:24:57,958
[Ji Hoo in elementary school]

240
00:25:19,446 --> 00:25:22,148
[Ji Hoo in college]

241
00:26:03,689 --> 00:26:05,724
Ga Eul...

242
00:26:07,093 --> 00:26:11,797
Didn't you say your father had tenure of 20 years at his company?

243
00:26:11,797 --> 00:26:15,250
It hasn't even been that long since he was promoted to assistant manager.

244
00:26:17,980 --> 00:26:24,206
Why did they suddenly force only your dad to resign?

245
00:26:26,805 --> 00:26:29,831
Why did they do it?

246
00:26:44,394 --> 00:26:45,883
Seriously?

247
00:26:45,883 --> 00:26:51,956
Shinhwa's Group subcontracting company forced Ga Eul's dad to resign, all those things in just one morning?

248
00:26:51,956 --> 00:26:54,607
It looks like it.

249
00:26:54,607 --> 00:26:59,052
I was wondering why she didn't do anything after the wedding.

250
00:26:59,052 --> 00:27:02,022
Then again it seems Ji Hoo has been put into a mess too.

251
00:27:02,937 --> 00:27:03,956
Ji Hoo, why?

252
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:07,687
It seems Chairman Kang is going to take over Ji Hoo's foundation as well.

253
00:27:07,687 --> 00:27:08,476
What?

254
00:27:08,476 --> 00:27:12,445
The development of the new art center in Song-do has already been postponed.

255
00:27:12,445 --> 00:27:14,954
Then...

256
00:27:14,954 --> 00:27:16,860
this is all?

257
00:27:16,860 --> 00:27:20,378
Her plan to destroy the one, Geum Jan Di.

258
00:27:40,781 --> 00:27:42,883
Grandfather...

259
00:27:45,051 --> 00:27:47,237
Jan Di, I'm glad you came.

260
00:27:47,237 --> 00:27:48,756
Why?

261
00:27:48,756 --> 00:27:51,033
Did you miss me in that short period of time?

262
00:27:51,033 --> 00:27:53,994
You and your delusional thinking!

263
00:27:53,994 --> 00:27:58,169
Jan Di, since you're here, why don't you take that boy out of here?

264
00:27:58,169 --> 00:28:03,088
He's completely stuck on me and won't move an inch.

265
00:28:03,088 --> 00:28:05,539
It's suffocating.

266
00:28:10,154 --> 00:28:12,613
Why aren't you guys getting out of here?

267
00:28:12,613 --> 00:28:15,692
On such a beautiful spring day!

